Subject: in_dxf: a block with no xref path is local, not an xref

Bound-xref blocks (names like "A$C7B302068") and other local blocks can
carry a stray xref bit (0x4) in their BLOCK_RECORD table flag (group 70).
in_dxf's SET_CTRL_BIT(4, blkisxref) copied that bit onto the BLOCK_HEADER,
so LibreDWG marked the block as an external reference — and AutoCAD/
BricsCAD then render every insert of it as a giant unresolved "Xref
<name>" placeholder instead of the block's geometry (whole furniture
layers vanished on a re-saved plan). ODA writes blkisxref 0 for the same
input.

A real xref must have an xref path. When the BLOCK entity is linked to its
header, clear blkisxref/xrefoverlaid if the block has no xref pathname —
it is local. Verified: the block decodes byte-identical to ODA and the
plan renders correctly in BricsCAD; all 254 unit tests pass.

Co-authored-by: Claude Fable 5 <noreply@anthropic.com>

--- a/src/in_dxf.c
+++ b/src/in_dxf.c
@@ -13727,6 +13727,20 @@ dxf_blocks_read (Bit_Chain *restrict dat, Dwg_Data *restrict dwg)
                           _hdr->base_pt.x = _obj->base_pt.x;
                           _hdr->base_pt.y = _obj->base_pt.y;
                           LOG_TRACE ("BLOCK_HEADER.base_pt = BLOCK.base_pt\n");
+                          // A bound/local block (e.g. "A$C..." from a bound
+                          // xref) keeps a stray xref bit in its BLOCK_RECORD
+                          // flag 70, but a real xref must have an xref path.
+                          // No path => it is local: clear blkisxref, or
+                          // AutoCAD/BricsCAD render it as an unresolved Xref.
+                          if (_hdr->blkisxref
+                              && bit_empty_T (dat, _obj->xref_pname))
+                            {
+                              _hdr->blkisxref = 0;
+                              _hdr->xrefoverlaid = 0;
+                              LOG_TRACE ("BLOCK_HEADER.blkisxref = 0 "
+                                         "(no xref path, local block)\n");
+                            }
